{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 METADATA MANAGER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This Script provides an easy to use interface to create and manage DDP Metadata markers in Reaper. Key features:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clear and easy to use interface to enter Metadata\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Multiple possible workflows to create DDP markers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Elaborate error checking in regards to the CD Red Book standard\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Responsive UI\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Playlist Folders\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Features: Create Pro Tools style playlists in Reaper. Record on automatically numbered playlists, then assemble your takes on a target playlist. Cycle through your playlists or move specific playlists to the top. Toggle solo (listen) to specific playlists. All actions (should) work with playlists hidden. All actions (should) work on grouped tracks using Reapers native track grouping system. Use the "Record Arm Lead" parameter. Running an action on one track will run it for all grouped tracks. Even without their playlists showing! If you ever accidentally move a playlist of a grouped track or want to restore order in your playlist folders you can automatically sort them again by number.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
